[{"category":"section","location":"api.html#API-reference","page":"API","text":"","title":"API reference"},{"category":"section","location":"api.html#Index","page":"API","text":"Modules = [NetworkOutbreaks]","title":"Index"},{"category":"type","location":"api.html#NetworkOutbreaks.HAS","page":"API","text":"HAS <: OutbreakAlgorithm\n\nHierarchical Adaptive Sampling algorithm.\n\nMaintains per-node hazards in a complete binary sum tree of length 2 * N_tree (where N_tree = nextpow(2, N)).  Event selection is O(log N) via a single tree descent; per-event updates touch O(Δ) nodes each at O(log N) cost, giving O(Δ log N) total.  For fixed-degree graphs (regular, Erdős–Rényi) this is O(log N) per event regardless of rate heterogeneity — a deterministic guarantee that CompositionRejection provides only in the amortised sense.\n\nSupports TimeVaryingNetwork.\n\nSee docs/HAS_PLAN.md for design details.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NetworkOutbreaks.HAS"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NetworkOutbreaks.OutbreakModel-Tuple{AbstractVector{Symbol}, Any, AbstractVector{OutbreakTransition}}","page":"API","text":"OutbreakModel(compartments, infectious_set, transitions; name)\n\nConvenience constructor where infectious_set is an iterable of compartment names that should be flagged as infectious.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NetworkOutbreaks.OutbreakModel"},{"category":"type","location":"api.html#NetworkOutbreaks.StaticNetwork","page":"API","text":"StaticNetwork{G<:AbstractGraph}\n\nWraps a fixed contact graph. Created automatically when a plain AbstractGraph is passed to OutbreakSpec.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NetworkOutbreaks.StaticNetwork"},{"category":"type","location":"api.html#NetworkOutbreaks._TVN_Update","page":"API","text":"TimeVaryingNetwork{G<:AbstractGraph}\n\nA contact network whose topology changes over time. graph is the mutable base graph (state at tspan[1]). updates is a sorted (by .t) vector of edge updates applied during a simulation.\n\nEach update is a NamedTuple with fields:\n\nt      :: Float64  — simulation time at which the update fires\nsrc    :: Int      — source node\ndst    :: Int      — destination node\naction :: Symbol   — :add or :remove\n\nThe graph is deepcopy-ed at the start of each trajectory so simulate and simulate_ensemble are safe to call repeatedly on the same spec.\n\nCurrently supported algorithms: DirectSSA, NextReaction, and HAS. CompositionRejection raises an ArgumentError if combined with a TimeVaryingNetwork.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NetworkOutbreaks._TVN_Update"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NetworkOutbreaks._has_leaf-Tuple{Int64, Int64}","page":"API","text":"_has_leaf(v, N_tree) → Int\n\nIndex of the leaf cell for node v (1-indexed) in the sum tree.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NetworkOutbreaks._has_leaf"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NetworkOutbreaks._has_sample_node-Tuple{Vector{Float64}, Int64, Int64, Random.AbstractRNG}","page":"API","text":"_has_sample_node(tree, N_tree, n, rng) → Int\n\nDescend the sum tree from the root using uniform draws to select a node proportional to its hazard.  Returns the 1-indexed node number, or 0 if the total rate is zero (absorbing state).  O(log N).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NetworkOutbreaks._has_sample_node"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NetworkOutbreaks._has_update!-Tuple{Vector{Float64}, Int64, Float64}","page":"API","text":"_has_update!(tree, leaf_idx, new_h)\n\nSet tree[leaf_idx] = new_h and propagate updated partial sums up to the root.  O(log N).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NetworkOutbreaks._has_update!"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NetworkOutbreaks.final_size-Tuple{OutbreakTrajectory}","page":"API","text":"final_size(traj; recovered = nothing)\n\nTotal fraction of nodes that have been infected at least once during the trajectory. Computed from final_infection_counts. The recovered keyword is accepted for API symmetry but ignored — the per-node infection counter is the more direct quantity.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NetworkOutbreaks.final_size"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NetworkOutbreaks.initial_state-Tuple{OutbreakSpec, Random.AbstractRNG}","page":"API","text":"initial_state(spec, rng) -> Vector{Int}\n\nMaterialize a per-node compartment-index vector from the spec's seed specification.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NetworkOutbreaks.initial_state"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NetworkOutbreaks.mean_curve-Tuple{OutbreakEnsemble, Symbol}","page":"API","text":"mean_curve(ens, sym; tgrid = nothing)\n\nReturn (t, μ) where t is a common time grid and μ[k] is the mean count in compartment sym at time t[k] across the ensemble.\n\nIf tgrid is nothing, a 200-point linear grid covering the spec's tspan is used.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NetworkOutbreaks.mean_curve"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NetworkOutbreaks.quantile_band-Tuple{OutbreakEnsemble, Symbol}","page":"API","text":"quantile_band(ens, sym; q = (0.025, 0.975), tgrid = nothing)\n\nReturn (t, lo, hi) where lo[k] and hi[k] are the q[1] and q[2] quantiles of compartment sym at time t[k] across the ensemble.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NetworkOutbreaks.quantile_band"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NetworkOutbreaks.reinfection_histogram-Tuple{OutbreakTrajectory}","page":"API","text":"reinfection_histogram(traj; L = nothing)\n\nHistogram of per-node infection counts at the end of traj. Returns a Vector{Int} of length L+1 (or maximum + 1 if L is nothing) where index p+1 holds the number of nodes infected p times. Counts above L are saturated into the top bucket — matching the convention of with_reinfection_counting.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NetworkOutbreaks.reinfection_histogram"},{"category":"function","location":"api.html#NetworkOutbreaks.simulate","page":"API","text":"simulate(spec::OutbreakSpec; algorithm = DirectSSA(),\n         seed::Integer = rand(UInt64), keep::Symbol = :counts)\n    :: OutbreakTrajectory\n\nRun a single stochastic simulation. keep is one of:\n\n:counts    — only times + compartment counts at each event (default).\n:events    — additionally store the full event log.\n\nseed is forwarded to a fresh Xoshiro RNG; pass the same seed to reproduce a run exactly (single-threaded).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NetworkOutbreaks.simulate"},{"category":"method","location":"api.html#NetworkOutbreaks.simulate_ensemble-Tuple{OutbreakSpec}","page":"API","text":"simulate_ensemble(spec; nsims, seed = rand(UInt64), parallel = false, kwargs...)\n\nRun nsims simulations of spec. Each child receives a deterministic sub-seed derived from the master seed and its trajectory index, so a fixed seed gives the same ensemble in sequential mode and with parallel = true, independent of Julia's thread count.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NetworkOutbreaks.simulate_ensemble"},{"category":"section","location":"vignettes.html#Vignettes","page":"Vignettes","text":"Worked examples for NetworkOutbreaks.jl. Source .qmd files live in vignettes/.\n\n01_reinfection_validation — Reinfection Validation: SIS on a Random 3-Regular Network\n02_algorithm_comparison — Algorithm Comparison: DirectSSA, NextReaction, and CompositionRejection","title":"Vignettes"},{"category":"section","location":"index.html#NetworkOutbreaks.jl","page":"Home","text":"Stochastic compartmental epidemic simulation on contact networks, with adapters for EdgeBasedModels.jl and NodeBasedModels.jl.","title":"NetworkOutbreaks.jl"},{"category":"section","location":"index.html#Installation","page":"Home","text":"using Pkg\nPkg.add(url = \"https://github.com/epirecipes/NetworkOutbreaks.jl\")","title":"Installation"},{"category":"section","location":"index.html#Quick-start","page":"Home","text":"using NetworkOutbreaks, Graphs, StableRNGs\n\nmodel = OutbreakModel([:S, :I, :R],\n                      [:I],\n                      [OutbreakTransition(:S, :I, 0.5, :infection),\n                       OutbreakTransition(:I, :R, 1.0, :spontaneous)])\n\ng    = random_regular_graph(500, 4; rng = StableRNG(42))\nspec = OutbreakSpec(model   = model,\n                    network = g,\n                    initial = SeedFraction(:I => 0.02),\n                    tspan   = (0.0, 50.0))\n\ntraj = simulate(spec; algorithm = DirectSSA(), seed = 1)\nens  = simulate_ensemble(spec; nsims = 40, seed = 2, parallel = true)","title":"Quick start"},{"category":"section","location":"index.html#Algorithms","page":"Home","text":"Type Description TimeVaryingNetwork\nDirectSSA() Gillespie direct method — O(N) per event ✓\nNextReaction() Gibson–Bruck next-reaction — O(log N) per event ✓\nCompositionRejection() Slepoy et al. 2008 — O(1) amortised ✗\nHAS() Hierarchical Adaptive Sampling — O(log N) deterministic ✓","title":"Algorithms"},{"category":"section","location":"index.html#Documentation-contents","page":"Home","text":"Vignettes — algorithm comparison and reinfection-counting validation.\nAPI reference — exported types and functions.","title":"Documentation contents"},{"category":"section","location":"index.html#Companion-packages","page":"Home","text":"EdgeBasedModels.jl — edge-based compartmental models on configuration-model networks.\nNodeBasedModels.jl — node- and pair-level approximations.","title":"Companion packages"},{"category":"section","location":"index.html#License","page":"Home","text":"NetworkOutbreaks.jl is licensed under the MIT License.","title":"License"}]
